vectorData.altText: That's right!  The calcaneal tendon(B) is also known as the Achilles tendon. When its associated muscles contract, the tendon pulls across the posterior aspect of the talocrural joint, causing plantarflexion.

the tendon of insertion of the muscles in the posterior superficial compartment. Follow it to the tuberosity of the calcaneus. Because these muscles, when they contract, pull up on the calcaneus, they push the toes down, thus plantarflex the talocrural joint.

the gastrocnemius muscle. Notice that they originate proximal to the knee joint, and so are capable of contributing to flexion of the knee as well as plantarflexion of the talocrural joint. Observe that the two heads of the gastrocnemius fuse to form a single muscle belly, which is identifiable in surface anatomy as the “calf” of the leg.
